Unnecessary requirements for public procurement applications shall be excluded by law
The legislation may lay down exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session, the State Duma plans to consider in the second reading a bill establishing the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, the participants of which can be only subjects of small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The draft law is developed in accordance with the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the development of small and medium-sized enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of the application from procurement participants - small and medium-sized enterprises.
And also - about the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, design and composition of the application for participation in the purchase are set by the customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, the mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, extracts, the period of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable with the period of submission of applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such a procurement and reducing the number of participants in the procurement," the explanatory note to the bill reads.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of the application from procurement participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will eliminate the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," the explanatory note reads.
