The authorities of the Moscow region told about the fate of closed landfills
In the suburbs continue to close landfills of solid household waste.
This year, the authorities promise to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 existing landfills are being upgraded to modern waste disposal complexes.
But this option is not possible for every polygon - many of them are overgrown with dense residential buildings.
After the polygon is closed, it stands for recultivation - the body of the polygon is overflowing with soil, degassing and infiltrate drainage systems are installed.
This allows you to stop the chemical processes inside the landfill, so that it does not ignite, does not emit stench, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former landfill remains to rise up a useless pile among the surrounding residential buildings.
Why not make something useful out of it?
For example, in the Ruza, where just a few days ago the rehabilitation of the polygon "Annino", the authorities are considering the option of making a ski slope out of a pile.
This polygon, which was operated from 1976 to 2016, expanded so that it went beyond the boundaries of the allocated land for it.
Therefore, during recultivation, it was necessary to buy out neighboring plots, de facto already stuffed with garbage for a long time.
"Some time will pass, the training ground will "sit down", the fortress will be built, and we will think what can be done to make it useful.
The ski resort is eye-catching,” the head of the Ruz district, Nikolai Parfenov, told reporters.
