Woman dumped her husband’s body in a pit and poured concrete under Belgorod
In the Belgorod region, a woman confessed to the murder of her own husband, whom she threw into a pit with waste and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional government of the Russian Federation.
It is noted that the suspect lived in a marriage with the murdered since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel, the woman decided to kill.
"When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his hands and feet, put a plastic bag on his head and squeezed with a pillow.
When the husband stopped giving signs of life, she wrapped the body in a carpet, took it out into the yard and hid it in a septic tank.
The next day she called a concrete mixer and filled the pit with concrete,” the office said.
The woman later said her husband was missing.
Relatives of the deceased appealed to the police, who opened the hole and recovered the body.
The investigation intends to ask the court to arrest the suspect.
The criminal investigation is currently ongoing.
